column2: Year of skill additions on LinkedIn.
ISIC Name and Index according to the ISIC Rev. 4 industry classification (1 digit level), available for six ISIC tradable and knowledge-intensive sectors (e.g. ISIC Index: B, C, K, J, M, R).

Detailed industry Name according to the LinkedIn industry classification (approximately 2 digit ISIC Rev. 4 level), detailing industries composing the six ISIC Rev. 4 tradable and knowledge-intensive sectors (e.g. 'ISIC_section_name').

Skill groups categorize the 50,000 detailed individual skills into approximately  250 skills groups. For example, web development (skill group), may be composed of java, html etc. skills. Some skill groups may be excluded as a result of data quality considerations.

Skill groups are ranked at the 'industry_name' (approximately ISIC Rev. 4 two digit) level. The top 10 skill groups ranked 1 to 10, are the most-distinctive and most-represented skill groups (skill_group_name) by LinkedIn members in a given industry (industry_name).
